<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Consideration" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Consideration,</orth> 1) meditation, reflection: <cit><quote>startles and frights c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c., like an angel, came,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 28</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and in thy best c. check this hideous rashness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 152</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let's to supper, and drown c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 2, 45</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) regard: <cit><quote>dubbed on carpet c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.258" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 258</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>albeit --s infinite do make against it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 102</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 66</bibl> <cit><quote>(give it quick c.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 196</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>